WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:11.089 --> 00:00:16.000
Those, who like sauerkraut will like recipe cabbage in Georgian.

00:00:16.019 --> 00:00:17.820
It has hot taste.

00:00:17.820 --> 00:00:22.810
It stimulates the appetite and makes this snack a frequent guest on our table.

00:00:22.810 --> 00:00:25.480
For this recipe we will need:

00:00:25.480 --> 00:00:31.519
Cabbage. I took half of a large head of cabbage.

00:00:31.519 --> 00:00:33.110
Beet.

00:00:33.110 --> 00:00:36.170
One large or several small carrots.

00:00:36.170 --> 00:00:40.160
Garlic, hot pepper.

00:00:40.160 --> 00:00:43.840
Sugar and salt.

00:00:43.840 --> 00:00:46.520
Take the cabbage.

00:00:46.520 --> 00:00:51.500
We cut it into large chunks.

00:01:09.100 --> 00:01:13.117
We shift it into a bowl.

00:01:19.080 --> 00:01:23.260
Take beets.

00:01:23.260 --> 00:01:25.930
We cut it into small pieces.

00:01:25.930 --> 00:01:30.000
Large strips.

00:01:39.700 --> 00:01:42.734
Add to cabbage.

00:01:43.120 --> 00:01:47.650
Rub carrots on a coarse grater.

00:01:47.650 --> 00:01:52.130
If there is a special grater for Korean carrot, you can use it.

00:01:52.130 --> 00:01:56.100
Then you get a long and beautiful carrots.

00:01:59.300 --> 00:02:04.400
Also add carrots to the vegetables.

00:02:07.050 --> 00:02:12.529
Now hot pepper.

00:02:12.529 --> 00:02:15.500
We cut it into strips.

00:02:24.879 --> 00:02:29.800
Squeeze garlic through a press.

00:02:38.809 --> 00:02:45.800
Gently stir. Can be stirred by hands.

00:02:55.349 --> 00:03:00.359
We shift into a glass jar.

00:03:03.809 --> 00:03:09.900
I think that it is better not to mix and shift the layers one by one.

00:03:20.719 --> 00:03:25.700
Press down slightly.

00:03:27.829 --> 00:03:29.809
Will prepare the brine.

00:03:29.809 --> 00:03:32.179
Take 1 liter of water.

00:03:32.179 --> 00:03:38.189
Add 2 tbsp of salt.

00:03:38.189 --> 00:03:41.139
Half a cup of sugar.

00:03:41.139 --> 00:03:45.339
Incidentally, this is the proportion for 1 liter of water.

00:03:45.339 --> 00:03:50.209
1 cup of 9% vinegar.

00:03:50.209 --> 00:03:52.899
I have a sweet peas.

00:03:52.899 --> 00:03:54.009
Immediately add it to the cabbage.

00:03:54.009 --> 00:03:57.939
I think it will not be superfluous.

00:03:57.939 --> 00:04:02.100
Set brine on fire and bring to a boil.

00:04:04.200 --> 00:04:09.289
Brine boiled. Turn off the heat.

00:04:09.289 --> 00:04:14.000
Let it cool down a bit - about five minutes.

00:04:14.000 --> 00:04:16.200
Then I will pour it into the jar.

00:04:16.449 --> 00:04:21.400
Fill cabbage with brine.

00:04:37.200 --> 00:04:40.800
Cover with a lid.

00:04:40.830 --> 00:04:45.200
We will make vacuum.

00:04:55.000 --> 00:04:59.409
Lights up red light - turn off.

00:04:59.409 --> 00:05:00.669
Close.

00:05:00.669 --> 00:05:03.099
After 4-5 hours, the cabbage will be ready.

00:05:03.099 --> 00:05:07.000
Crunch with pleasure and enjoy!

